                                                                                                                           17                                                                                      Demi saves suicidal teen after Twitter threat
          NICK ALLEN                                    
	Los Angeles, March 22: Actresses Demi Moore and Nia Vardalos, the star of My Big Fat Greek Wedding, have helped to save the life of a suicidal teenager after he threatened on Twitter to hang himself.        
	 The 18-year-old sent Moore a message through the social networking website saying he was going to commit suicide at his home near Orlando, Florida. His message said: Im about to go hang myself from a tree outside my house and end my life. I have no reason to live anymore. Moore responded within a minute asking if the teenager was serious, and he replied that he was.        
	Her Twitter account has more than 2.5 million followers and among those watching the exchange was Vardalos, who called a suicide hotline and gave the mans name and where he lived. Police went to the teenagers home and found him sitting at his computer desk crying. He told officers he did not know what to do with himself without help.        
	 The teenagers mother told officers he was very emotional and diagnosed with obsessive compulsive disorder.                     THE DAILY TELEGRAPH                                                                                                                                                  
